6.22.25  9:40 pm   what is art and how can i make more of it?

6.22.25  6:15 pm   Been peeking into ontology recently. I'm curious, do you believe that anything could exist without something else to perceive it? I first thought of it as a matter of "tree falls, no one is around to hear it, does it make a sound?", but I think it might be closer to, "could a tree exist to fall in the first place if not for perception?"

      maybe 'perception' is required, but i would argue that the threshhold for what counts as perception may be lower than any of us have ever dreamed of
